description.plain:
Moneybagg Yo (born September 22, 1991) is a platinum-selling recording artist from Memphis, Tennessee who is affiliated with Yo Gotti. He is a signee of Gotti’s Collective Music Group (CMG) in partnership with N-Less Entertainment and Interscope Records.

Following the August 2018 release of Bet On Me, Bagg found the hip-hop spotlights with release of RESET and 43VA HEARTLESS. In 2020, he released his third studio album, Time Served, and its deluxe edition.

Bagg climbed the Billboard Hot 100 in 2021, securing his first No. 1 album with A Gangsta’s Pain, supported by hit singles such as “Wockesha” and “Time Today.”

songs.title: Said Sum

description.plain:
In the lead single for his mixtape Code Red, Moneybagg Yo dismisses his haters who have lots to say, but can’t back up their words. What matters to him is that he’s rich and they’re broke.

The song was first previewed on Bagg’s Instagram on June 29, 2020, the day before its release.
